      <para id="id18586378">Continuing we will get back h(2) and h(3) as expected.</para>
      <para id="id18586383">In part (a) if we evalue H(4) we will see it is equal to H(1), and in part (b) if we evaluate h(4) we will see it is equal to h(1). The reason is that H(k) is periodic and h(n) is assumed periodic. This example illustrates the frequency sampling method of FIR filter design (<link document="m11287"> sectionn </link>).</para>
